                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003"> f. iiir(ecto), top</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003"> f. iiir(ect0), bottom</locus><desc> Five <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> holding books adorned with crosses (four gospel writers and Paul?)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003"> f. iiv(erso), top</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> holding a cross and riding in the clouds (right), appears to a man (center)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003"> f. iiv(erso), bottom</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/> (center). Berutiwit stands on the right; a spear bearer stands on the left</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003"> f. iiir(ecto), top</locus><desc> The manifestation of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1105HolyWoman">Holy Woman</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> (seated right). Angels crown her (above right). She holds up flowers towards five people (standing right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003"> f. iiir(ecto), bottom</locus><desc> Five <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref>, three of whom are holding books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004"> f. iiiv(erso), top</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1039Magi">The Three Magi</ref> (kneeling right) extend gifts to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> and baby <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> (seated center). <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8417Salome">Salome</persName> stands behind Mary (right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004"> f. iiiv(erso), bottom</locus><desc> Four <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#ivr(ecto)" facs="004"> f. ivr(ecto), top</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1016Flight">Flight into Egypt</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#ivr(ecto)" facs="004"> f. ivr(ecto), bottom</locus><desc> Two <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> spearing enemies</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11"><locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="005"> f. iiv(erso), top</locus><desc> Two <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> holding books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es (center) with angels with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and <term key="scabbard" ana="#scabbard"/> standing to the right and the left</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12"><locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="005"> f. ivv(erso), bottom</locus><desc>A king (seated center) gestures toward two partially clad people (left); two men administer the sacraments to four people (right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d13"><locus target="#13r" facs="017"> f. 13r, top</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1105HolyWoman">Holy Woman</ref> (right, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>?) kneels before six saints (left)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d14"><locus target="#13r" facs="017"> f. 13r, bottom</locus><desc> Three <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> saints holding prayer sticks</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d15"><locus target="#13v" facs="018"> f. 13v, top</locus><desc> Three <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d16"><locus target="#13v" facs="018"> f. 13v, bottom</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> spears an enemy (left); An angel and a saint look on (right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d17"><locus target="#31r" facs="035">Fol. 31r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1016Flight">Flight into Egypt</ref> (upper right); <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5764Joseph">Joseph</persName> takes <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> by the hand (lower right); Two angels holding books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es and a saint look on (left)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d18"><locus target="#31v" facs="036">Fol. 31v</locus><desc> Six <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> s lift up <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> (upper left); Mary and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3725Elizabet">ʾElsābeṭ</persName> (upper right); an equestrian saint spears an anemy and two saints holding books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es (lower)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d19"><locus target="#46r" facs="050">Fol. 46r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1015Flagellation">Flagellation of Jesus</ref> (upper left); four saints (upper right, all four hold books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es and two hold processional <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es); The flogging of of a blind-folded <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> (lower right); two saints (lower left)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d20"><locus target="#46v" facs="051">Fol. 46v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1002Annunciation">Annunciation</ref> to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> (upper left); a saint looks on (upper right); two equestrian saints spear enemies (lower)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d21"><locus target="#83r" facs="087">Fol. 83r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref> (upper left). Seven saints, most holding books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es surround (upper right and lower)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d22"><locus target="#83v" facs="088">Fol. 83v</locus><desc> Two <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> s spear enemies (upper); three saints standing (lower)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d23"><locus target="#86r" facs="090">Fol. 86r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1112JesusBurial"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1112JesusBurial</span></ref> by Nicodemus and Joseph of Arimathea with <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> looking on (upper left); four saints surround (upper right and lower)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d24"><locus target="#86v" facs="091">Fol. 86v</locus><desc> Two <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> s holding books (upper); two equestrian saints spearing enemies (middle); <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> (lower center) teaching the twelve disciples (eight lower left; four lower right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d25"><locus target="#127r" facs="131">Fol. 127r</locus><desc> A variation on the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1086StrikingHead">The Striking of the Head, ኵርዓተ፡ ርእሱ፡</ref> (upper right), surrounded by five saints (right, left, and below)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d26"><locus target="#127v" facs="132">Fol. 127v</locus><desc> Three <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> (upper); two equestrian saints spearing enemies (lower)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d27"><locus target="#145r" facs="149">Fol. 145r</locus><desc> Three <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> (upper); <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> before the twelve (lower)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d28"><locus target="#145v" facs="150">Fol. 145v</locus><desc> Two <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> holding books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es greet one another (upper left); an equestrian saint spearing an enemy (upper right); the resurrection of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> raising <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1386Adam">Adam</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3926Eve">Eve</persName> (lower left); saint <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName> surrounded by leopards (lower right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d29">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#21v" facs="026">fols. 21v, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                    a line of alternating red and black dots with a full stop is used as a section divider throughout (e.g, <locus target="#2v #21r #26r #28v" facs="007 025 030 033">2v, 21r, 26r, 28v</locus>);
                    multiple full and half stops are used as section dividers throughout
                    </decoNote>
